Handling the online status of an Android app can be done using the ConnectivityManager class, which is part of the Android SDK. This class allows you to check the current network state, including whether the device is connected to a network and what type of connection it is using.
To check the online status, you can use the following code:


```
ConnectivityManager cm = (ConnectivityManager)getSystemService(Context.CONNECTIVITY_SERVICE);
 NetworkInfo activeNetwork = cm.getActiveNetworkInfo();
 boolean isConnected = activeNetwork != null && activeNetwork.isConnectedOrConnecting();
```
To share the online status between different ViewModels, you can use a shared ViewModel or a singleton class that holds the online status and can be accessed by all ViewModels.
Another approach is to use a LiveData object which can be observed by multiple ViewModels and update the status accordingly.


```c
lass NetworkHelper {
 private MutableLiveData<Boolean> isConnected = new MutableLiveData<>();
 public NetworkHelper() {
 ConnectivityManager cm = (ConnectivityManager)getSystemService(Context.CONNECTIVITY_SERVICE);
 NetworkInfo activeNetwork = cm.getActiveNetworkInfo();
 isConnected.postValue(activeNetwork != null && activeNetwork.isConnectedOrConnecting());
 }
 public MutableLiveData<Boolean> getIsConnected() {
 return isConnected;
 }
}
```
This way you can observe the LiveData object in your ViewModel and react to the changes in the online status.


```c
lass MyViewModel extends ViewModel {
 private NetworkHelper networkHelper = new NetworkHelper();
 public MyViewModel() {
 networkHelper.getIsConnected().observe(this, new Observer<Boolean>() {
 @Override
 public void onChanged(Boolean isConnected) {
 // update UI or perform actions based on the online status
 }
 });
 }
}
```
You can also use SingleLiveEvent or Event to notify the ViewModel of the changes in the online status.
It's important to note that you need to check the state of the network periodically and call `postValue()` on the MutableLiveData or `setValue()` on the SingleLiveEvent or Event when the network state changes.

