```
In this example, the `ini_set` function is used to enable persistent connections and set the maximum number of persistent connections and links to -1, which means no limit. The `p:` prefix before the host name tells the MySQLi extension to use a persistent connection.

It's important to keep in mind that persistent connections can lead to issues if not implemented and managed properly, such as running out of connections, so it's important to monitor and adjust the number of connections used by the application. It's also important to note that persistent connections are not always the best option, it depends on the specific use case and requirements of the application. It's a good idea to test the performance of the application with and without persistent connections to determine which option is the most suitable.

