```
It's also important to note that when comparing a variable to NULL using the comparison operator `==`, the comparison will also return true if the variable is not set (i.e., it has never been assigned a value). To check if a variable is both NULL and not set, you can use the `isset` function in conjunction with the `is_null` function.


