Yes, the expansion of (7x + 5)^8 can be written in summation (sigma) notation as:

\begin{align\*}
(7x + 5)^8 &= \sum\_{k=0}^8 C(8,k) \* (7x)^{8-k} \* (5)^k \
&= \sum\_{k=0}^8 \binom{8}{k} (7x)^{8-k} (5)^k
\end{align\*}

where C(n, k) is the binomial coefficient "n choose k" and the summation runs from 0 to 8, inclusive.

